QIKVRT V45.12 Windows CMD Trailing-Backslash-Safe Full Repository

Author / Product Owner: Ingolf Lohmann
Created: 2026-06-20T15:23:53Z

Operational boundary:
- Local Windows verification remains PowerShell-only and does not require Python.
- CMD wrappers no longer pass `%~dp0` with a trailing backslash directly into
  quoted PowerShell arguments. The repository root is normalized before handoff.
- Build ZIP and hash strictly separate Root and OutDir. OutDir may be missing and
  is created before use; Resolve-Path is never applied to a missing output path.
- Optional Python helpers still go through a runtime resolver and must never leak
  Windows App Execution Alias exit code 9009 as repository verification result.
- Real GitHub merge/commit/push/release is implemented via PowerShell + git + gh.
- No real GitHub release may be claimed without persisted owner acceptance and
  strict remote-effect evidence.
